      <option name="classThreshold" value="80" />
      <option name="methodThreshold" value="80" />
      <option name="warnMissingCoverage" value="true" />
    </inspection_tool>

    <!--
      ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      VERIFY-THEN-PROMOTE — resolved 2026-07-11. Every candidate from the
      original list (docs/inspection-profile-tiers.md) was traced to a
      specific inspectionId via JetBrains Inspectopedia and promoted into
      the ERROR block above. None were left unresolved.

      A handful of legacy inspections (finally, divzero, fallthrough,
      ValueOfIncrementOrDecrementUsed) have Inspectopedia pages that show
      two different-looking ID strings — one labeled "By ID" (documented as
      "used to locate inspection in e.g. Qodana configuration files", and
      matching the page's own URL slug) and a separately-labeled "Inspection
      ID" field that sometimes disagreed. Local empirical verification via
      a Dockerized Qodana run was inconclusive: unrecognized inspection IDs
      don't produce a distinct warning, they simply produce zero findings —
      indistinguishable from a valid ID that has no matching violation in
      the sample sources (proven by including a deliberately-bogus ID in
      the test profile and observing it produce no error either). The "By
      ID" value was used for all four, since it is the one Inspectopedia
      consistently and explicitly documents for this exact use case. Treat
      the first real Qodana CI run as the canonical confirmation for these
      four specifically — if any of them produce a schema/profile-loading
      warning, swap in the alternate "Inspection ID" value noted inline.
      ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    -->
  </profile>
</component>
